<subSubSection id="6D837C85102EFFB1DBE2FE244D1C2AD8" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="25262F0E102EFFB1DBE2FE244D1C2AD8" blockId="11.[151,1437,150,501]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C102EFFB1DBE2FE244D0E2AA4" bold="true" box="[199,315,367,393]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="E299548D102EFFB1DA65FE244D9B2AA4" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[320,430,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C102EFFB1DA65FE244D9B2AA4" box="[320,430,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">A. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D102EFFB1D988FE244F252AA4" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[685,784,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setifer">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C102EFFB1D988FE244F252AA4" box="[685,784,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">A. setifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
newly described below from southern 
<collectingRegion id="E75DE1EC102EFFB1DF92FE24492A2AA4" box="[1207,1311,367,393]" country="Indonesia" name="Sulawesi Utara" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Sulawesi</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5D8E6F9E102EFFB1DE0DFE2449AD2AA4" box="[1320,1432,367,393]" name="Indonesia" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
, in colour pattern. Although the antennal segments IV and V of 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D102EFFB1D87FFED84FF52A80" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[858,960,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setifer">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C102EFFB1D87FFED84FF52A80" box="[858,960,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">A. setifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
each bears a series of 7–11 setae arranged in a longitudinal row on ventral surface (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B102EFFB1D95EFEFC4ED52AFC" box="[635,736,438,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 124–130" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1882,1906]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,181,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-17@31.[170,1417,181,1858]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 124–130. Asianthrips setifer, sp. n., female (mac). (124) Head &amp; pronotum; (125) Antennal segments III–VIII, ventral aspect; (126) Metanotum &amp; pelta; (127) Basantra–mesopresternum (holotype); (128) Mesopresternum (a paratype); (129) Fore wing; (130) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404920" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404920/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Fig. 125</figureCitation>
), this species do not have such a series of setae, at least in macropterae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
